HEADWORD: Light-horseman
<hw>Light"-horse`man</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧t"h⟦ocir⟧rs`m⟦ait⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>-men</plw>
<pr>(l⟦imac⟧t"h⟦ocir⟧rs`m⟦eit⟧n)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A soldier
who serves in the light horse. See under 5th <er>Light</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A West Indian fish of the genus
<gen>Ephippus</gen>, remarkable for its high dorsal fin and brilliant
colors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

